post_text: At this point, RCW Community Education does not have enough registrants to support the Jaguar Jamboree after school day care program. Therefore, it will NOT begin on the first day of school. We are extending the deadline to register to Thursday, August 27, 2020. If we have enough registrants by that time, the program will begin on Monday, August 31, 2020. To register, please visit www.rcw.k12.mn.us ‚Äì Community Education ‚Äì Jaguar Jamboree ‚Äì Registration to print and complete the registration form. It can be brought to the District Office or emailed to communityed@rcw.k12.mn.us.

post_text:
As of Tuesday Aug.4 the MSHSL board of directors have voted to move Volleyball and Football to the Spring (tentative start of March 15th). Cross Country and Girls Tennis are still on for the Fall. Those practices start on Monday Aug. 17th.
MSHSL still needs to clarify all these changes, so please be patient as we wait for more information. In the meantime if you have any questions please email Mr. Johnson (djohnson@rcw.k12.mn.us).

Thank you for your continued support!

post_text: RCW will have four School Board vacancies on the ballot at this November‚Äôs election. A recording of MSBA‚Äôs Running for School Board Webinar can now be accessed on YouTube at: https://youtu.be/BhUZMzM2Vmo. The webinar covers basics such as how to file for the board, reasons to serve on the board ‚Äî and reasons not to serve on a board, job duties of school boards, and how boards function as a team. post_text:
Renville County West will begin distance learning on Monday, March 30th. At this time, distance learning is set to end on May 4th. However, if that date changes, we will communicate that information at a later time. Critical links and information regarding distance learning will be available on our website at www.rcw.k12.mn.us no later than Friday, March 27th.

Food service for all students aged 18 and under and day care services for students 12 years and under of essential employees will continue throughout the distance learning period.

Thank you so very much for your patience and understanding during this difficult and unprecedented time. We are committed to the continued education and well-being of all RCW students.

Amid growing concerns about the COVID-19 pandemic, the remainder of the girls state basketball tournament and boys section/state basketball tournaments have been canceled. The safety of all concerned is paramount.

Section Speech Tournament events for the week of March 15-21 have been postponed indefinitely.

Additional details and information on other upcoming events including Spring Activities will be shared later today.
